7.8.21  3:12 am   Is only liking commercially-produced "popular"-style music a sign of a superficial mind?

     Even if you look into the musical traditions of non-Western countries, you'll find yourself outside of the "comfort zone" that non-niche car radios propagate, not to mention what happens when you look into millennia-old musical traditions (perhaps it's off-putting to lump the rich history of music into an "older music" category, but I'm not well-equipped to mention specifics. hopefully you understand what I mean by "popular" music and its out group). If there are so many styles of music to look into but you never look beyond what's available on popular music stations, what does this tendency say about your sense of curiosity, intellectual depth, and other such personal attributes?

     (I was using a general you for the previous sentence, by the way).
